 York City [[strip club]]. [[Nova (Richard Rider)|Richard Rider]] and Vance Astrovik make a trip to check on her.<ref>\'\'New Warriors\'\' #18</ref>\\n\\nShe later joins a new version of Psionex, which reforms under the new [[Asylum (comics)|Asylum]] (formerly the villain known as Darkling). This teams dedicates itself to crime-fighting but falls apart after a civilian with a heart condition dies during an encounter. Persuasions returns to Genetech for observation but later appears again as an exotic dancer.{{Issue|date=July 2009}}\\n\\n===\'\'Civil War\'\'===\\n{{Main|Civil War (comics)}}\\n\\nDuring the Civil War event, Pretty Persuasions is apprehended by Baron Zemo and his [[Thunderbolts (comics)|Thunderbolts]]. She is shown imprisoned in energy rings, with other villains, having been captured long before the Thunderbolts were given official allowance to take down villains.<ref>\'\'Thunderbolts\'\' #103</ref> She faces the \'choice\' of working as an agent of the government, or going to jail for not registering with the Superhuman Registration Act and her past crimes. Persuasions, along with many other recruits, are forced into aiding the Thunderbolts and Earth\'s heroes in a battle against the cosmic powered [[Grandmaster (Marvel Comics)|Grandmaster]] and dozens of super-powered opponents. The recruits are seen being overwhelmed and their final fate is not yet made clear.{{Issue|date=July 2009}}\\n\\n===Dark Reign===\\nPretty Persuasions and Psionex are revealed as members of the Initiative\'s Maryland team.<ref>\'\'Avengers: The Initiative\'\' #26</ref>\\n\\n== Powers and abilities==\\nPretty Persuasions can stimulate a person\'s pleasure centers psionically, meaning she can excite, as well as to increase the erotic  urges/sexual desires of others. With her power she can seduce and control other people, usually men. In addition, she can create many kinds of psionic energy weapons, usually preferring whips.\\n\\n==References==\\n<references />\\n\\n[[Category:Comics characters introduced in 1990]]\\n[[Category:Female supervillains]]\\n[[Category:Fictional dancers]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics mutates]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics superheroes]]\\n[[Category:Marvel Comics supervillains]]\\n\\n\\n{{Marvel-villain-stub}}"}]}}}}'